[debug] [2026-04-12T19:43:47.110Z] <<< [apiv2][body] GET https://firebaseextensions.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/hkmjbs-streaming/instances {"instances":[{"name":"projects/hkmjbs-streaming/instances/rtdb-limit-child-nodes","createTime":"2025-01-08T06:07:33.081479Z","updateTime":"2026-01-18T05:35:35.931032Z","state":"ACTIVE","config":{"name":"projects/hkmjbs-streaming/instances/rtdb-limit-child-nodes/configurations/cb783c1e-222f-4cc8-a112-7a0321248dda","createTime":"2026-01-18T05:30:29.477127Z","source":{"name":"projects/firebaseextensions/sources/f8aff791-2365-4b78-bd57-228da9bb4a5c","packageUri":"https://storage.googleapis.com/firebase-extensions-packages-prod/firebase-rtdb-limit-child-nodes-0.1.15-4e8c4087-86bd-44b6-b0f3-4be3baadbfc4.zip","hash":"d52819b50a79f2abbd19a4ef3cf8a82c5798b5f6491d12aee3a85cb78bb17edd","extensionRoot":"/","spec":{"specVersion":"v1beta","name":"rtdb-limit-child-nodes","version":"0.1.15","description":"Limits the number of nodes to a specified maximum count in a specified Realtime Database path.","roles":[{"role":"firebasedatabase.admin","reason":"Allows the extension to delete nodes from your Realtime Database instance."}],"resources":[{"name":"rtdblimit","type":"firebaseextensions.v1beta.function","propertiesYaml":"eventTrigger:\n  eventType: providers/google.firebase.database/eventTypes/ref.create\n  resource: projects/_/instances/${param:SELECTED_DATABASE_INSTANCE}/refs/${param:NODE_PATH}/{messageid}\nruntime: nodejs20\n","description":"Listens for new child nodes in your specified Realtime Database path, checks if the max count has been exceeded, then deletes the oldest nodes first, as needed to maintain the max count.","deletionPolicy":"DELETE"}],"billingRequired":true,"author":{"authorName":"Firebase","url":"https://firebase.google.com"},"contributors":[{"authorName":"Chris Bianca","email":"chris@csfrequency.com","url":"https://github.com/chrisbianca"},{"authorName":"Invertase","email":"oss@invertase.io","url":"https://github.com/invertase"}],"license":"Apache-2.0","releaseNotesUrl":"https://github.com/firebase/extensions/blob/master/rtdb-limit-child-nodes/CHANGELOG.md","sourceUrl":"https://github.com/firebase/extensions/tree/master/rtdb-limit-child-nodes","params":[{"param":"NODE_PATH","label":"Realtime Database path","type":"STRING","description":"What is the Realtime Database path for which you want to limit the number of child nodes?","required":true,"example":"path/to/limit","validationRegex":"^\\S+$","validationErrorMessage":"Path cannot have spaces."},{"param":"SELECTED_DATABASE_INSTANCE","label":"Realtime Database","type":"STRING","description":"From which Realtime Database instance do you want to limit child nodes?\n","required":true,"default":"${DATABASE_INSTANCE}","example":"my-instance","validationRegex":"^([0-9a-z_.-]*)$","validationErrorMessage":"Invalid database instance"},{"param":"MAX_COUNT","label":"Maximum count of nodes to keep","type":"STRING","description":"What is the maximum count of nodes to keep in your specified database path? The oldest nodes will be deleted first to maintain this max count.","required":true,"example":"10","validationRegex":"^\\d+$","validationErrorMessage":"Invalid MAX_COUNT, must be a positive integer."}],"preinstallContent":"Use this extension to control the maximum number of nodes stored in a Firebase Realtime Database path.\n\nIf the number of nodes in your specified Realtime Database path exceeds the specified max count, this extension deletes the oldest nodes first until there are the max count number of nodes remaining.\n\n#### Additional setup\n\nBefore installing this extension, make sure that you've [set up a Realtime Database instance](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database) in your Firebase project.\n\n### Billing\nTo install an extension, your project must be on the [Blaze (pay as you go) plan](https://firebase.google.com/pricing)\n\n- This extension uses other Firebase and Google Cloud Platform services, which have associated charges if you exceed the service’s no-cost tier:\n  - Cloud Functions (Node.js 10+ runtime. [See FAQs](https://firebase.google.com/support/faq#extensions-pricing))\n  - Firebase Realtime Database\n","postinstallContent":"### See it in action\n\nYou can test out this extension right away!\n\n1.  Go to your [Realtime Database dashboard](https://console.firebase.google.com/project/${param:PROJECT_ID}/database/${param:PROJECT_ID}/data) in the Firebase console.\n\n1.  In the path `${param:NODE_PATH}`, add more than ${param:MAX_COUNT} child nodes.\n\n1.  In a few seconds, you'll see the number of child nodes reduced to ${param:MAX_COUNT}.\n\n### Using the extension\n\nIf the number of nodes in `${param:NODE_PATH}` exceeds the max count of ${param:MAX_COUNT}, this extension deletes the oldest nodes first until there are ${param:MAX_COUNT} nodes remaining.\n\nWe recommend adding data via pushing, for example `firebase.database().ref().child('${param:NODE_PATH}').push()`, because pushing assigns an automatically generated ID to the node in the database. During retrieval, these nodes are guaranteed to be ordered by the time they were added. Learn more about reading and writing data for your platform (iOS, Android, or Web) in the [Realtime Database documentation](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/).\n\n### Monitoring\n\nAs a best practice, you can [monitor the activity](https://firebase.google.com/docs/extensions/manage-installed-extensions#monitor) of your installed extension, including checks on its health, usage, and logs.\n","readmeContent":"# Limit Child Nodes\n\n**Author**: Firebase (**[https://firebase.google.com](https://firebase.google.com)**)\n\n**Description**: Limits the number of nodes to a specified maximum count in a specified Realtime Database path.\n\n\n\n**Details**: Use this extension to control the maximum number of nodes stored in a Firebase Realtime Database path.\n\nIf the number of nodes in your specified Realtime Database path exceeds the specified max count, this extension deletes the oldest nodes first until there are the max count number of nodes remaining.\n\n#### Additional setup\n\nBefore installing this extension, make sure that you've [set up a Realtime Database instance](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database) in your Firebase project.\n\n### Billing\nTo install an extension, your project must be on the [Blaze (pay as you go) plan](https://firebase.google.com/pricing)\n\n- This extension uses other Firebase and Google Cloud Platform services, which have associated charges if you exceed the service’s no-cost tier:\n  - Cloud Functions (Node.js 10+ runtime. [See FAQs](https://firebase.google.com/support/faq#extensions-pricing))\n  - Firebase Realtime Database\n\n\n\n\n**Configuration Parameters:**\n\n* Realtime Database path: What is the Realtime Database path for which you want to limit the number of child nodes?\n\n* Realtime Database: From which Realtime Database instance do you want to limit child nodes?\n\n\n* Maximum count of nodes to keep: What is the maximum count of nodes to keep in your specified database path? The oldest nodes will be deleted first to maintain this max count.\n\n\n\n**Cloud Functions:**\n\n* **rtdblimit:** Listens for new child nodes in your specified Realtime Database path, checks if the max count has been exceeded, then deletes the oldest nodes first, as needed to maintain the max count.\n\n\n\n**Access Required**:\n\n\n\nThis extension will operate with the following project IAM roles:\n\n* firebasedatabase.admin (Reason: Allows the extension to delete nodes from your Realtime Database instance.)\n","displayName":"Limit Child Nodes"},"fetchTime":"2025-02-18T19:33:22.944196Z","lastOperationName":"projects/firebaseextensions/operations/38b2c726-6cad-4873-8308-71d7dec2afda","state":"ACTIVE"},"params":{"MAX_COUNT":"100","NODE_PATH":"matchRounds","SELECTED_DATABASE_INSTANCE":"hkmjbs-streaming-default-rtdb"},"populatedPostinstallContent":"### See it in action\n\nYou can test out this extension right away!\n\n1.  Go to your [Realtime Database dashboard](https://console.firebase.google.com/project/hkmjbs-streaming/database/hkmjbs-streaming/data) in the Firebase console.\n\n1.  In the path `matchRounds`, add more than 100 child nodes.\n\n1.  In a few seconds, you'll see the number of child nodes reduced to 100.\n\n### Using the extension\n\nIf the number of nodes in `matchRounds` exceeds the max count of 100, this extension deletes the oldest nodes first until there are 100 nodes remaining.\n\nWe recommend adding data via pushing, for example `firebase.database().ref().child('matchRounds').push()`, because pushing assigns an automatically generated ID to the node in the database. During retrieval, these nodes are guaranteed to be ordered by the time they were added. Learn more about reading and writing data for your platform (iOS, Android, or Web) in the [Realtime Database documentation](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/).\n\n### Monitoring\n\nAs a best practice, you can [monitor the activity](https://firebase.google.com/docs/extensions/manage-installed-extensions#monitor) of your installed extension, including checks on its health, usage, and logs.\n","extensionRef":"firebase/rtdb-limit-child-nodes","extensionVersion":"0.1.15","systemParams":{"firebaseextensions.v1beta.function/location":"asia-east2","firebaseextensions.v1beta.function/memory":"256","firebaseextensions.v1beta.function/vpcConnectorEgressSettings":"VPC_CONNECTOR_EGRESS_SETTINGS_UNSPECIFIED","firebaseextensions.v1beta.function/minInstances":"0"}},"lastOperationName":"projects/hkmjbs-streaming/operations/33e95038-fdca-4173-87c3-a8bd887eb70e","serviceAccountEmail":"ext-rtdb-limit-child-nodes@hkmjbs-streaming.iam.gserviceaccount.com","lastOperationType":"UPDATE","etag":"590d005fb800097a308bd3bc2321fdaa5046e6bb80f66309bcde191c31d93ef4"},{"name":"projects/hkmjbs-streaming/instances/rtdb-limit-child-nodes-189d","createTime":"2026-01-18T05:43:26.796462Z","updateTime":"20